{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Eclairs","content":["Place a shallow roasting tin in bottom of oven and preheat to 200°C. Line 2 baking trays with baking paper and set aside.","Place butter, 150 g water and salt in mixing bowl then heat <b>5 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>.","Add flour and blend <b>1 min\/speed 8<b>. Remove mixing bowl lid and leave to cool for 5 minutes.","After this time and without measuring cup, mix <b>speed 3<b>, adding eggs one at a time through hole in mixing bowl lid, stopping when eggs are fully incorporated. Insert measuring cup and blend <b>1 min\/speed 10<b>. Transfer mixture to a piping bag fitted with a 1 cm plain nozzle then pipe 18-20 fingers, 3 cm long, on prepared baking trays.","Place trays in oven then carefully pour 100 g cold water into roasting tin in bottom of oven. Bake for 20-25 minutes (200°C) or until risen, golden brown and crisp. Meanwhile, clean mixing bowl. Remove trays from oven and slice a small slit on the side of each éclair to release steam. Return to oven for 5 minutes (200°C) to dry out then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely."]},{"title":"Creamy Cods Roe","content":["Place cods roe, lemon juice and garlic in mixing bowl then blend <b>30 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Place a jug on mixing bowl lid and weigh in rapeseed oil then set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Mix <b>speed 3<b>, while slowly pouring rapeseed oil from jug onto mixing bowl lid, letting it drizzle around measuring cup in a thin stream onto rotating blades.","Add hot water. Place jug on mixing bowl lid and weigh in peanut oil. Mix <b>speed 3<b>, while slowly pouring peanut oil from jug onto mixing bowl lid, letting it drizzle around measuring cup in a thin stream onto rotating blades. Let mixture rest for 5 minutes then transfer to a piping bag fitted with a 1 cm plain nozzle. Chill in fridge for 30 minutes until needed. Clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Horseradish Cream","content":["Place horseradish in mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and pour boiling water over then leave to soak for 10 minutes.","Place drained grated horseradish in mixing bowl. Add vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper then blend <b>5 sec\/speed 3<b>."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Add cream and whip <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Whip again <b>20 sec\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a piping bag fitted with a 0.5 cm nozzle then chill in fridge until needed.","When éclairs are completely cool, pipe cods roe into them through slits. Pipe a line of horseradish cream on top then garnish with caviar and mustard cress before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Eclairs","content":["80 g unsalted butter, diced","250 g water, cold","2 pinches fine sea salt","120 g plain flour","3 medium eggs"]},{"title":"Creamy Cods Roe","content":["125 g smoked cods roe, membrane removed, cut in pieces and soaked in cold water for 2-3 hours","25 g lemon juice","1 garlic clove","75 g rapeseed oil","1 Tbsp water, hot","75 g peanut oil"]},{"title":"Horseradish Cream","content":["25 g fresh horseradish, peeled, cut in pieces","2 Tbsp water, boiling","1 Tbsp white wine vinegar","1 pinch caster sugar","1 tsp Dijon mustard","1 pinch fine sea salt, or to taste","1 pinch ground black pepper, or to taste","200 g double cream"]},{"title":"To Serve","content":["55 g caviar, or avrugar","mustard cress, to garnish"]}],"id":"r121155","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-cn2Go7Ir3T0\/XZMt6wtAt1I\/AAAAAAAAZ_A\/JrAjymM5ceoqtBkWRJ1gxpnDyHzNwhcpQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_3sjw1hImLqWu8seZ.png","title":"Smoked Cods Roe Eclairs with Horseradish Cream","publishedAt":"2016-11-21T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"2.8 g","fat":"16.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"5.3 g","calories":"772 kJ \/ 185 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays and baking paper, roasting tin, piping bag and nozzle, wire rack, jug, oven, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["These are fun and fabulous, a bit of a blast from the past. However, with éclairs trending again I could not resist resurrecting this savoury beauty. Make small little éclairs for a canapé party or larger shapes for a finger buffet. You could splash out and use caviar if you wish."],"basicInfo":["advanced","30m","1h 55m","20 portions"]}